    "scopeAndContentNote": "Part 1, Air Force planes take off to investigate \"flying saucer\" rumors. Shows blips on a, radar screen at Wash., D.C., airport. Shows a sector of N.Y. City's skyline where a \"saucer\" was reported. Gen. Samford tells newsmen there is no cause for worry. Part 2, Argentine street crowds mourn for Eva Peron; crowds pass her bier in Buenos Aires. Part 3 shows an exhibit of dolls, including automatons, in Paris. Part 4, Stevenson talks to Bloomington, Ill., voters; rides in a motorcade through Springfield, Ill.; and poses on the porch of the Governor's mansion. Part 5 shows distance races and decathlon events at the Olympic Games, Helsinki. Ashenfelter, Zatopek, and Mathias win events.",
    "naId": 99731,
    "soundType": "Sound"
